nce for its\nsouthern side where enhanced illumination impinges from the Sco OB2 association\nand the O star zeta Oph. A good correlation is found between the H2\nfluorescence and a previously mapped 21-cm excess emission. The H2 fluorescence\nemission in LDN1780 has been modelled using a PDR code; the resulting values\nfor H2 column density and the total gas density are consistent with the\nestimates derived from CO observations and optical extinction along the line of\nsight.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 16 Jun 2018 12:38:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-09-12"}
